Fill and boil your kettle. Pop the @egg noodle nests{2} in a #saucepan{}. Cover with boiling water and cook on medium heat until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

When cooked, drain in a #colander{} and run under cold water to stop the noodles cooking further.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a large #frying pan{} over high heat. Add the @British pork mince{240%g} and sprinkle on the @Thai style spice mix{1}.

> Be careful it's spicy! Add less if you're not a fan of heat.

Cook until browned, breaking it up with a #wooden spoon{} as it cooks, ~{5-6%minutes}.

While the pork is cooking, halve the @green pepper{1} and remove the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Trim the @spring onions{2} then slice thinly. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Halve the @lime{1/2}. Add the green pepper to the pork and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Mix the @Ketjap Manis{50%ml} with the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and @honey{15%g} together in a #bowl{}. Squeeze in the lime juice.

Add the spring onions to the pan and pour the sauce onto the pork. Bring to a simmer. Bubble for ~{2%minutes}.

Stir the cooked noodles and half the coriander into the pork. Stir to coat the noodles and cook until everything is piping hot.

Share the noodles between your #bowls{} and finish with a sprinkle of remaining coriander. Enjoy!